  "text": "We remark that it is not easy to construct these trial states in the torus geometry since the parent Hamiltonian generating each state as the zero-energy ground state is unknown. On the other hand, in the spherical geometry, one can obtain the amplitudes of each state in second quantization basis by making use of the Jack polynomial representation [CITATION_1] . While these trial states could be important in some parameter regimes of the bilayer quantum Hall system, in this work, we are only interested in the single-layer quantum Hall states, which can be obtained by antisymmetrizing the simple Abelian bilayer quantum Hall states such as the Halperin (330) and (551) states.",
